ignificant management judgment to estimate total costs (labor hours, shared costs, satellite material costs, expected technological changes).\n- Deferred revenue as of December 31, 2025 ($12,116 million total) primarily relates to Space agreements and Connectivity enterprise and government contracts (which includes Starshield).\n\n### Conclusion\nStarshield is classified within the **Connectivity** segment (specifically the "Enterprise & Government" revenue line), but the S-1 provides **no standalone revenue contribution disclosure** for Starshield. Its financial performance is aggregated with other enterprise and government connectivity contracts rather than being broken out separately.\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}',
